[10:39.10]	But not away to-morrow!
[10:41.01]IACHIMO	O, I must, madam:
[10:42.39]	Therefore I shall beseech you, if you please
[10:45.68]	To greet your lord with writing, do't to-night:
[10:49.11]	I have outstood my time; which is material
[10:52.27]	To the tender of our present.
[10:54.57]IMOGEN	I will write.
[10:55.82]	Send your trunk to me; it shall safe be kept,
[10:59.11]	And truly yielded you. You're very welcome.
